<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1007,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1048,1074]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Scapular tubercles and setae ahead of rear shield margin; tibia fused with tarsus, empodium entire; dorsal opisthosoma with a median ridge; coxal-genital region lacking annuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1007,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
This genus consists of 14 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[647,893,1132,1158]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[752,809,1132,1157]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
